The article discusses the tragic event of a white supremacist attacking the Tree of Life Synagogue in Pittsburgh, resulting in the deaths and injuries of innocent people. It highlights the importance of recognizing this act as a harm against all of society, not just a specific group. The article acknowledges that hate crimes have been on the rise in the United States and emphasizes the need to address domestic terrorism and reduce gun violence. It mentions President Joe Biden's actions to protect houses of worship and strengthen measures against acts of hate. The article expresses solidarity with the Squirrel Hill and Jewish communities and renews the commitment to combat antisemitism.